8.How does the number of confirmed cases vary across different provinces/states?¶

province_confirmed_cases=df.groupby('Province/State')['Confirmed'].sum().reset_index()
province_confirmed_cases.dropna(subset=['Province/State'])
confirmed_cases_sorted = province_confirmed_cases.sort_values(by='Confirmed', ascending=False)

import pandas as pd 
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

plt.xticks(rotation=40)
plt.xlabel('Province/State')
plt.ylabel('Total Confirmed Cases')
plt.title('Confirmed Cases Across Different Provinces/States')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

15.How does the mortality rate vary across different countries/regions?¶

In [36]:
country_stats = df.groupby('Country/Region')[['Confirmed', 'Deaths']].sum().reset_index()
country_stats['Mortality Rate (%)'] = (country_stats['Deaths'] / country_stats['Confirmed']) * 100
country_stats_sorted = country_stats.sort_values(by='Mortality Rate (%)', ascending=False)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
plt.bar(country_stats_sorted['Country/Region'], country_stats_sorted['Mortality Rate (%)'], color='red')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)

plt.ylabel('Mortality Rate (%)')
plt.title('Mortality Rate Across Different Countries/Regions')
plt.tight_layout()

df['Last Update'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Last Update'],format='mixed')
df = df.groupby('Last Update')['Confirmed'].sum().reset_index()
df['New Confirmed Cases'] = df['Confirmed'].diff().fillna(0)
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(df['Last Update'], df['New Confirmed Cases'], marker='o', linestyle='-', color='b')
plt.xlabel('Last Update')
plt.ylabel('New Confirmed Cases')
plt.title('Trend of New Confirmed Cases Over Time Globally')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

20.What is the trend of active cases over time globally¶

In [49]:
# Convert 'ObservationDate' to datetime if it's the correct column for dates
df['ObservationDate'] = pd.to_datetime(df['ObservationDate'], format='mixed')

# Calculate active cases
df['Active Cases'] = df['Confirmed'] - df['Deaths'] - df['Recovered']

# Group by date and sum the active cases
daily_active_cases = df.groupby('ObservationDate')['Active Cases'].sum().reset_index()

# Plot the trend of active cases over time
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.plot(daily_active_cases['ObservationDate'], daily_active_cases['Active Cases'], marker='o', linestyle='-', color='purple')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Active Cases')
plt.title('Trend of Active Cases Over Time Globally')
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
